{
  "stem": "2966.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes, there was no problem, because everybody still-- most everybody still lived in-- in the same neighborhood and the same home, because traditionally, you lived-- it's not that you grow up here and you move away to a different part of the country or the city.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "People stuck in the same neighborhoods.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Young people, when they got married, they lived right next door to their parents or grandparents.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that's why you went out on the street, you had half your family in your neighborhood.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that remained the same during the Russians.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Some people, of course, they were displaced.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Some were sent to Siberia.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "A few-- and they were very lucky.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And some people stayed just the way they were.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Things started to change in Septem-- in June of 1941 when Hitler declared war on Russia.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think it was June 21st.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We woke up in the morning, and we heard that Hitler crossed the new border with the France and Allies, which were Russia.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there was great chaos.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And within a couple days, people-- the Russian army, whoever was still-- they-- they didn't stand up to fight at all.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they were just retreating, and-- by truck, by train, and by any means.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They were just running east.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And at that time, quite a few of our people-- mostly Jews, I would say-- that had any higher positions under the communists [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] went with the Russian army.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They went east to Russia.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, my family never thought of leaving, because our fathers, that generation, they fought in the First World War.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they were associated with the Austrian army, which was treating the Jews very well.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And most of them said, it's-- nothing can go wrong, because the Germans are very cultured people.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
